<TEXT>
a london newspaper said sunday that the united 
states has sent a secret envoy to iran to discuss reestablishing 
diplomatic links 
the observer in an unattributed story did not identify the 
official but said he is apparently a close friend of president 
reagan and went to tehran two weeks ago it said the envoy was 
traveling under the name of clark 
the observer said the envoy met middleranking iranian 
officials who asked for assurances that any arms embargo against 
them as proposed by the united nations should be delayed until 
early this summer 
the united states is seeking a un ban on arms sales because 
iran has not accepted a ceasefire agreement in its eightyear war 
with iraq 
there have been no diplomatic relations since the us embassy 
in tehran was stormed nov 4 1979 and held for 444 days with 
diplomats and others kept hostage inside 
