<TEXT>
leaping luggage and sniffing out sneaky smugglers 
the latest addition to miami international airports k9 corps has 
racked up impressive credits in his first two months on the beat 
his human colleagues say 
king a romping 2yearold cross between a black labrador 
retriever and a german shorthaired pointer has a nose that makes 
news 
since the us customs service gave king to metrodade police 
he has sniffed out 86000 in drugscented cash 347 pounds of 
cocaine and helped collar four suspects said police lt larry 
martin 
the beloved rookie one of three canines used by metrodade 
police at the airport has all but matched the 400pound career 
total of ringo who just retired after about a decade martin said 
hes an upandcoming dog martin said of the enthusiastic 
pooch who with handler detective ken buzzi graduated from the 
us customs dog training school in front royal va 
king and buzzi were still getting used to the domestic flight 
areas of miami international after their december graduation when 
they made their first score dec 17 
a man carrying christmas presents on a flight from denver fit 
the profile of a smuggler denver police had been suspicious 
the man agreed to a search and king alerted to a drug odor 
in his packages more than 40000 in drugtainted cash was 
discovered buzzi said 
the fact that a specially trained dog identified the money as 
having been associated with narcotics was probable cause to seize 
it buzzi said 
soon afterward king found a similar amount of drugtainted cash 
packed in a mercedes benz 
the two occupants of the car were arrested and are awaiting 
trial in dade county circuit court buzzi said 
kings abilities also led to the discovery of 185 pounds of 
cocaine and the arrest of two eastern airlines employees on feb 1 
the next day he sniffed out 155 pounds of cocaine concealed 
underneath the floor in the belly of an l1011 aircraft he 
detected 7 pounds of cocaine on an earlier search to bring his 
total to 347 pounds martin said 
i worked mostly narcotics for the last 16 years said buzzi 
the biggest seizure i made was 600 pounds and it took me almost 
10 years but working with a detector dog weve found almost 400 
pounds in the first two months we were back from school 
were both still a green team ive been a police officer for 
18 years but i feel like a rookie again its like a whole new 
career he said 
while king has a superfine nose he is not perfect buzzi 
said 
king gets tired sometimes while working his eighthour shift 
but so far hes been on the money he said 
detector dogs cannot sniff the enormous volume of luggage 
freight and planes used to smuggle narcotics and money through this 
primary port of entry for drugs buzzi said 
any dog and its handler are only as good as the watchful 
authorities who suggest likely targets 
it was mostly luck and being in the right place at the right 
time buzzi said 
</TEXT>
