thousands of students marched through london 
saturday waving banners chanting and banging drums to protest the 
governments proposed education reform bill 
police who closed several main roads to traffic estimated 
about 10000 demonstrators participated but the nationl union of 
students put the figure at 1500020000 
at one point some 200 students sat down for several minutes at 
the entrance to 10 downing street official residence of prime 
minister margaret thatcher police said there were no arrests 
during the demonstration 
student leaders say education secretary kenneth bakers measure 
will result in less student representation on college governing 
bodies and give industrial and commercial organizations too much 
influence in higher education and education for adults baker 
claims his bill will raise standards and improve the quality of 
state education 
the bill is now before parliament 
