<TEXT>
reagan administration officials said saturday 
that eric arturo delvalle recognized by the united states as 
panamas president decided on his own to go into hiding but that 
he remained in telephone contact with us diplomats in panama city 
delvalle is safe and in high spirits after escaping arrest 
and the struggle against the countrys military leader will 
continue delvalles envoy to washington said 
the permanent council of the organization of american states 
after a lengthy and at times heated debate saturday night on the 
situation in panama took no position on the turmoil there 
reagan administration officials denied participating in 
delvalles escape though they said the us ambassador to panama 
arthur h davis was in contact with delvalle by telephone 
they said they were not sure what delvalles next move would be 
president reagan who usually spends weekends at camp david 
md was at the white house receiving reports on the fastmoving 
situation 
the 30member oas council sidestepped a decision on whether to 
seat as panamas ambassador to the organization robert leyton the 
current envoy who is loyal to panamanian military chief manuel 
antonio noriega or larence chewning fabrega delvalles delegate 
there had been indications from officials of the american 
delegation that the council would seat neither man chosing instead 
to recognize soraya cano a panamanian career diplomat who is a 
member of the panamanian delegation to the oas 
the start of the formal council debate had been delayed for five 
hours while the envoys wrangled in private over the question of 
whom to credential as panamas representative 
but when the debate commenced shortly after 9 pm est no 
resolutions were offered dealing with that sticky question 
instead leyton was admitted to take part in the debate at least 
for the time being and he launched into a tirade against the 
united states accusing it of trying to destabilize his government 
i wish to somehow resolve the crisis in the government of 
panama leyton said but this is not the forum 
leyton steadfastly denied us charges that noriega has been 
involved in drug trafficking although the former panamanian 
ambassador to the united states gabriel lewis told the council 
we are suffering a new phenomenon narcomilitarism this 
narcotic militarism knows no frontier 
richard t mccormack the us ambassador to the oas said the 
united states could not accept the decision by the panamanian 
national assembly in which delvalle was deposed in a 10minute 
rump session 
in a riveting moment lewis had oas technicians play an 
audiocassette in which he had taperecorded the telephone 
conversation with delvalles wife mariela as panamanian military 
personnel surrounded her house after her husband had fled 
mrs delvalle in a trembling voice described how she had told 
the officers my husband isnt here nor are you going to find 
him 
a member of the us mission declining to be identified 
publicly indicated that a part of the problem for the oas 
ambassadors in deciding which panamanian representative to 
credential was that they had doubts about what stance they should 
take theyre afraid of doing something which might prejudice the 
position their government has taken on noriega the official said 
chewning said questions also had been raised about whether el 
salvadors ambassador ernesto rivas gallont had the right to 
request the special session with some ambassadors who support 
noriega opposing it 
chewning said those who oppose having the issue debated in the 
oas simply dont want the rest of the world to know whats going 
on in panama 
he said the ambassadors had not allowed him or leyton to address 
the gathering 
