<TEXT>
memorial services were held saturday 
for james h douglas jr former secretary of the air force 
douglas an attorney and investment banker died wednesday at 
his home in this northern chicago suburb he was 88 
douglas undersecretary and later secretary of the air force 
under president dwight d eisenhower presided over planning and 
construction of the air force academy in colorado springs colo 
douglas is credited with persuading the senate to approve the 
design of the academys chapel which was controversial at the 
time but which has since been hailed as an architectural triumph 
the cedar rapids iowa native graduated from princeton 
university after serving as an army officer in world war i he 
later spent a year at cambridge university in england before 
attending harvard law school 
after earning his law degree in 1924 douglas moved to chicago 
douglas held a high post in the us treasury department under 
presidents herbert hoover and franklin d roosevelt he returned to 
the army during world war ii 
by 1945 he was chief of staff of the armys air transport 
command 
eisenhower appointed douglas undersecretary of the air force in 
1953 and secretary in 1957 in 1959 douglas began a twoyear 
stint as deputy secretary of defense he was awarded the medal of 
freedom in 1960 
survivors include his wife elinor four sons and nine 
grandchildren 
