<TEXT>
fad health diets and marketplace gimmickry 
are giving americans a distorted view of the type and amount of 
foods needed to help prevent chronic disease according to a 
cornell university professor 
in a paper prepared for congressional testimony on tuesday t 
colin campbell said isolated studies taken out of context and 
promoted by special economic interests often trigger changes in 
the american diet that may actually be harmful 
too many americans believe in magic bullets too many 
corporations believe in profitrich products with very specific 
health claims said campbell 
such marketplace gimmickry he said does not help americans 
avoid the socalled diseases of affluence of osteoporosis and 
