in a paper prepared for the senate governmental affairs 
committee campbell recommended that the government establish a 
national research center to collect and analyze nutrition 
information so americans can receive more accurate information on 
diet and health 
campbell directed a massive study of the diet and lifestyle of 
6500 persons in 130 locations in the peoples republic of china in 
an effort to determine how nutrition affects such diseases as 
cancer and heart attack 
he said the study is not yet finished but results so far cast 
doubt on some of the popular american beliefs about nutrition and 
health 
among his observations 
american studies have shown that a serum cholesterol reading of 
180 milligrams per decaliter can reduce the risk of heart attack 
yet another us study showed that a reduction in cholesterol 
raises the risk of colon cancer campbell said that in china the 
cholesterol levels are far below the typical american level and 
the incidence of colon cancer also is low this shows he said 
that the study showing an increase in colon cancer with lower 
cholesterol is an experimental aberration 
excess calories may not be the sole cause of obesity campbell 
said he said the chinese consume about 20 percent more calories 
than do americans yet obesity is rare among the chinese he said 
chinese average only about 15 percent of their calories in the form 
of fat far below the typical american 
some american studies have suggested that an increase in fiber 
in the diet may lead to a loss of minerals campbell said the 
chinese consume about 34 grams of fiber per day versus about 10 
grams for most americans and yet the chinese show healthy levels 
of iron zinc and magnesium all important minerals 
</TEXT>
