chairman of lotus engineering 
special sessions include a panels look at the growing problem 
of disposing of automotive plastics as their use expands 
internally in the engine and passenger compartment and 
externally as more and more body parts are composed of stronger 
reinforced plastic substances 
the engineers also will discuss efforts to reduce release of 
ozonedepleting chloroflourocarbons or cfcs used in production 
automaking has been the main source of cfc emissions since the 
